Students then created art, played dreidel, ate lunch together, played on the playground, and most importantly fostered friendships with the impressive artists from @SandalGapStudio with intellectual disabilities. Segal students learned, questioned and shared. We look forward to a continued relationship with Sandal Gap and can’t wait to make more memories with our new friends.
